      "body" : "That's my point. It's much better to do this with armory, which is designed to be able to be used offline.\r\n\r\nThere is no use in running Bitcoin-Qt from a non-writable storage, as you need somewhere to store the block chain. Bitcoin-Qt is primarily a full P2P network node, and a wallet secondary.",
